   "source": [
    "Customer Segmentation for Strategic Growth & Decision Support \n",
    "Business Background \n",
    "Modern organizations operate in markets where customer heterogeneity is the norm rather than  the exception. Customers differ not only in demographics but also in: \n",
    "• Purchasing power \n",
    "• Engagement frequency \n",
    "• Channel preference (online vs physical) \n",
    "• Loyalty behavior\n",
    "\n",
    "Treating all customers as a single homogeneous group leads to: \n",
    "• Poor ROI on marketing spend \n",
    "• Inefficient loyalty programs \n",
    "• Underutilization of high-value customers \n",
    "• Over-investment in low-value segments \n",
    "\n",
    "The leadership team has therefore commissioned a data-driven customer segmentation  initiative to uncover hidden behavioral patterns that can inform targeted strategy and  operational planning. \n",
    "Because the organization does not already know how many customer types exist or what  defines them unsupervised machine learning (clustering) is the most appropriate analytical  approach. \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "54357684-240b-4fbe-93d2-9916cd09a5c1",
